10/06/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Slovenian and Croatian police seized a stash of cocaine Monday (June 9th) worth an estimated 5m euros.
Destined for the Croatian market, the drugs -- mixed with unidentified liquid -- had a total weight of 380kg.
Police in Zagreb said they came from Colombia.
After discovering and seizing the suspicious liquid at the Koper port, Slovenian police informed their Croatian counterparts and sent it to Zagreb.
Croatian police arrested two people in connection with the case.
(AFP, HRT, Makfax, Jutarnji List - 09/06/08)
